<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> do right by someone • put someone right</xh5><p> <i>do right by someone—</i>treat smb. fairly in moral or legal terms: I oppose this bill because it does not <u>do right by</u> our disabled veterans.</p><p><i>put someone right</i>—(also: put someone to rights) 1. make smb. well again: Since there is nothing wrong with him really, a placebo will <u>put him right</u>. 2. correct smb.’s ideas or information about smth.: His ignorance of the world is not abnormal for an American ... his advisors will <u>put him right</u> on foreign affairs.</p> </entry>
